metadata.name: EDDY #213
metadata.description:
An eddy is a circular movement of water counter to a main current. It reminds me of innovations in art, like a small countercurrent to the mainstream, surfacing new techniques and aesthetics. 

I hope that EDDY will brighten your days with its playful swirl of colors, inspired by the sea, the sky, the birds, and post-impressionist paintings.

Keyboard Controls:
[F] Fill the window.
[S] Save the current view in live mode as an image (default 1125x1500px).
[1] [2] [4] [6] Change resolution, 1.5K to 9K.
[R] Reverse course.

Made with p5js and shaders.

Created by elsif, 2022.12.

metadata.name: Hydro Gen #46
metadata.description:
Against the backdrop of texts about valuing water, Hydro Gen charts the ecological devastation and eventual revival of the Tisza river following what has been called one of the gravest environmental disasters in central Europe since Chernobyl.

Nature and humans here are bound within a single frame — havoc in the ecological system activates the breakdown of meaning in the human signifying system of language, but hidden in the wave of ecological disaster is a (re)generative love poem to water that bears witness to its multifaceted beauty and power. A second poem is generated as a soundtrack based on the displayed background text.

- - - - - CLICK TO START SOUND - - - - -

Hydro Gen is a collaborative work conceptualized and developed over the course of one week as part of NFT DEB Generative Dimensions 2022 Hackathon and Conference.

Kalen Iwamoto, lead artist, director

Vitalii Shumanskyi, lead programmer

Nayven Vignette, audio programmer

Tamás Béke, data analysis and visualization

metadata.name: Endeavor #117
metadata.description:
Endeavor is a generative system structured to create abstract mountains.

When I look at the outputs, I am reminded of the things I would like to achieve. I would be curious to know what comes to your mind when you ask yourself, "What is my goal? What do I intend to do?"

Controls:

'p' - Play an animation that draws the mountain layer by layer
'1' - Default, textured image
'2' - No border
'3' - Flat, non-textured image
'4' - Flat with no border

Each of the 128 editions chooses one of five forms, all of which explore variety in layout, shading, and color composition.

25% of the royalties for each edition will pass to the original minter.

Each output is generated from code written in p5js.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.

metadata.name: n Forms #149
metadata.description:
Hand-scrawled documentation of abstract structures. A journal from another realm.

Press 's' to save an image while in full-screen mode.

If you want to increase the resolution of the saved image, add e.g. &size=2000 after the live/fullscreen view URL to render the canvas at that specific pixel width (default = browser sized). This will be dependent on your system specifications, but outputs of up to 8000px wide, or above, should be possible.

Usually loads best in Chrome

metadata.name: CHIP #124
metadata.description:
A CHIP is being constructed by using two brushes that are painting on the board through deterministic noise, and then turned squared and pixelated and blended into each other, with colours selected from 21 different colour schemes. How many iterations, and the speed and size of the added parts determines the final composition. 

You can stop the iterations by pressing S, and download the current composition by hitting D, and restart/reload the iterations by pressing R.

Notes
The thumbnail generation takes a while and the render/iterations in non-GPU browser can be quite slow. Chrome/Firefox recommended.

metadata.description:
A degen has no goal, only path. But how will he go this path? 
Through the forest, by train or walking in the desert?

metadata.name: Un1 #117
metadata.description:
Un1 is inspired by Unicode block element characters, and my love of minimal and monochromatic art. 

With Un1 I was looking for the final result to have a slightly degraded or low-res look. To that end the pixel density is intentionally set low, (saved images [s] will be based on your browser window size) so that when the piece is enlarged or printed the output has a degraded look.

This artwork was coded using the p5.js library

metadata.name: Act One #69
metadata.description:
Act One, where the mannequin says “take me home and I will dance for you forever”.

This work is an exploration of using motion capture data to create digital paintings, and a little belated birthday ballet for #fxhashturnsone. 
20% of primary sales are donated to Three.js.
 
Keyboard Controls:
[P] Play / pause the dance. By default the dance is paused after a few seconds to render a painting.
[S] Save the current view (live mode).
[V] Capture a short webm video (live mode).

Mouse Controls (while dancing): 
[left drag] Rotate
[scroll] Zoom
[right drag] Pan
[right click] Save image

Best viewed in a desktop browser. The output may be different from the preview image if your frame rate is low, reducing the size of the browser window can help improve the frame rate.

Made using Three.js, canvas API and WebGL2.
The 3D model is based on https://sketchfab.com/3d-models/mannequin-dances-ballet-a24678a81a6f4b6d8f8ba0eb1a78e58b, using motion capture data from dancedb.eu. 
Test in Chrome v107.0.5304.107 and Safari v16.1.
License: CC BY-NC-SA 2.0

Created by elsif, 2022.11.

metadata.name: Happy #19
metadata.description:
Impressions of happiness, generated with code.  Press [P] to animate/pause.

Paint strokes are generated in 3D using three.js. You can drag the mouse to explore different views of the same painting. Interactions require a GPU.
Keyboard controls:
[S] Save the current view.
[P] Play / Pause animation.
[F] Fill the screen.
[1] Save 9:16 image, 3375 x 6000px.
[2] Save 3:4 image, 3000 x 4000px.
[3] Save 1:1 square image, 4000 x 4000px. 
[4] Save 16:9 image, 6000 x 3375px.

Elsif, 2022.04

objkt.name: Ode to Bugs and Happy Accidents #9

metadata.name: Ode to Bugs and Happy Accidents #9
metadata.description:
“If debugging is the process of removing software bugs, then programming must be the process of putting them in.”

― Edsger W. Dijkstra


This artwork is dedicated to happy accidents, mistakes, and bugs. Every key part of it is based on some sort of failure: wrong variable value, unstopped recursion, untimely function call. And sometimes it leads to pleasant results.

It was created to celebrate #fxhashturnsone event.

The earnings are partly donated to:
- Processing Foundation
- #TezosStandsWithUkraine

[a] - toggle animation
[1] - save PNG in low resolution
[2] - save PNG in medium resolution
[3] - save PNG in high resolution
[4] - save PNG in ultra-high resolution

Saving with high and ultra-high resolution may take a while, please be patient.


Made with love and p5js

By Collapsar Beauty
CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: CR Art Sessions //2 #35
metadata.description:
Grayscale, Hold the Line, and Mondrian walk into a bar. The bartender looks up and says, "What is this, some kind of art project?"

Grayscale responds, "No, we're just here for a drink."

Hold the Line adds, "But we can definitely add some color to the place if you want."

Mondrian chimes in, "I prefer to keep things simple and stick to the basics."

The bartender shakes his head and says, "I'll be the judge of that. What can I get you all?"

Grayscale orders a Guinness, Hold the Line asks for a gin and tonic, and Mondrian asks for a glass of white wine.

The bartender serves up the drinks and says, "That will be $15.50, please."

Grayscale pulls out a twenty-dollar bill and hands it to the bartender, saying, "Keep the change."

The bartender thanks him and says, "Thanks, Grayscale. You always know how to liven up the place."

Hold the Line raises his glass and says, "Cheers to that!"

Mondrian nods and clinks glasses with the others, and the three of them enjoy their drinks and the rest of their evening at the bar.

-----

Press "e" to save a png (3240*4500 or 4500*3240 px) while in live mode.

-----

Artwork by @cristianrohr (2022)

Made with P5js and <3.

metadata.name: Dithered Nostalgia #87
metadata.description:
Have you ever struck by a sudden surge of nostalgia?
Making you stop everything you did at that moment,
Trying hard to remember the memory behind it, and failed to do so?

Each of these lands hold a nostalgia unlocked,
Like how good nostalgia are, it’s dithered and full of holes.
Holes that can be filled with your own memories and interpretations.

• • •

The second collaboration of MEK.txt and IceRain in FXHash. This time using MEK.txt’s landscape pixelart series and its distinctive dithering textures, brilliantly translated into code by IceRain to pixel-perfect iterations.

Dithered Nostalgia is a step up from MEK.txt & IceRain’s first project (Bento Boxes), trying to make more sophisticated, more detailed and challenging things based on something they passionate about; landscape.

Controls:
[1] Set the resolution to Medium Resolution
[2] Set the resolution to High Resolution
